The issue with your code is that you are using the `Iterator.next()` method incorrectly. `Iterator.next()` returns the next element in the iterator, but it does not modify the iterator itself. Therefore, after you call `Iterator.next()` to check if the item is in the `myArray` list, you need to remove the iterator from the list using `Iterator.remove()`.

Here's the corrected code:
```scss
public void drop(String name) {
    for (Iterator<Item> iterator = myArray.iterator(); iterator.hasNext();) {
        Item count = iterator.next();
        if (count.getName().contains(name) && currentRoom.hasItem() == false) {
            currentRoom.addItem(count);
            currentMessage = "you have successfully dropped the item in the room";
            iterator.remove(); // remove the iterator from the list
            break; // exit the loop since we found a match
        } else if (count.getName().contains(name) && currentRoom.hasItem() == true) {
            currentMessage = "the room already has an item";
        } else {
            currentMessage = "you do not have that item";
        }
    }
}
```
With this change, the iterator will be removed from the `myArray` list after it has been checked for the item, and the loop will exit early since a match was found.
